snippet.textDisplay: Your work is incredible. Your depiction of 40k is far and away, the best there is, and I'll just go ahead and say it, GW needs to catch up to your fan fiction, not the other way around. Every little detail (THE GODDAMN CAPE MOVING WITH THE BOLTER SHOTS?!) and all the nuance you put in, both visual and cinematic is impeccable. You've done more in a handful of minutes than GW has done with their IP in a decade, and I feel like it bears repeating; they need to crib off your notes. I couldn't love this more. Your work is absolutely exquisite. If not more of this, I really hope to see more of your projects, whatever they may be.

snippet.textDisplay: In spending a bit of time thinking about this, that last episode looked like a combination of Xenos and AI at least to me. Could that have been the warp sure, but for some reason it screams Webway to me. And yes I know webway/eldar but other xenos had to have been aware of it as well as intelligent machines as well. What made me think this was the Golden Machine in that first room the Marines went through, it was being built to house something.  As well as the mechanical devices on the 2 psykers they fought. Then think about the Inquisitor being taken over by what sounded like a mechanical voice, and the marines attching those devices to the Orb reminded me of trying to insert a virus into a brain machine ( we have seen on sci fi movies ) to shut it down, but was to strong for the mechanicus tech.

Conversation:

3:53 – Inqusition Agent of Adeptus Mechanicus is hearing whispering when Sphere says: “Astartes” (probably the same one which in reality the Kill Team expirienced) And he started to focus.


4:04 - Caged sphere: “Who is there?” (Noticing somebody is overhearing)


4:07/4:08 - Spiked sphere: “I have failed brother.” (Voice is quieter, means further)


4:09/4:19 - Caged sphere: “We have all failed. The Astartes deny our touch (psychological shockwave). You must return. Break your seal.” (Voice is louder and more clear, means closer.)


4:19/4:20 - Spiked sphere: “Impossible. We will never survive.” (Voice is quieter, means further)


4:23 - Caged sphere: “You must take the Alpha / ...other” (Voice is louder and more clear, means closer.)
For me personally is: "You must take the other"
